  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals are typically obligated to report suspicious transactions or activities to the appropriate authorities. Specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Filing suspicious activity reports (SARs)\n3. Conducting customer due diligence\n4. Maintaining transaction records\n5. Training staff to recognize potential money laundering indicators\n\nHowever, I want to be clear that I cannot provide specific legal advice about money laundering reporting requirements.",
